candidates.body: Many changes that have accumulated over the past few months

candidates.title: Improvements for 0.1.0
candidates.body:
Well, this snowballed into a series of changes that I think makes this system `0.1.0` ready.

I found a safety issue related to `unstable_from_slice` not checking for equal bitwidths. This was a remnant of early design sloppiness that has now been completely fixed. Everything has much better testing now. The unsafety problem could only be accessed by end users using a hidden function with documentation telling end users not to use it (and `awint_macros` used it correctly), so I don't think it is an urgent issue, but I should yank 0.1.0-pre.0 as soon as I complete this.

Although it was the original purpose for this PR, `awint_dag` will have to remain incomplete for now.
